pattpack.tree
Interface BinaryTree<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>

All Known Implementing Classes:
Branch, Leaf
public interface BinaryTree<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>

This interface defines simple-minded binary (search) trees. Only the most elementary methods are defined. The interface exists for the implementation of an exercise about an Iterator pattern.

A binary tree is either a Leaf or Branch. Branches are decorated by an Object, and have a left and right child, that are binary trees. Leaves have no decorations or children.

insert

BinaryTree<E> insert(E x)
Construct a new tree which is the result of inserting of an element into in this binary tree. Elements are inserted in such a way that:
  • Elements in a tree are unique. Inserting an element that is already in a tree has no effect.
  • Every element in the left child of a branch precedes the branch's decoration.
  • Every element in the right child of a branch follows the branch's decoration.

Parameters:
x - The element to insert in a tree.
Returns:
A new tree representing this object with a new element inserted into it.

print

void print(int level)
Pretty print this tree. Rotate 90 deg clockwise to look at the output.

Parameters:
level - The print indentation level of this branch's decoration. The user calls this method with level=0.
